{  "Category": "Booking Related",  "Sub-Category": "When will I receive vehicle and crew (driver) details ?",  "Question": "My  ticket has been booked. When would I receive an update on the service / crew or driver details?

",  "Answer": "Most of the Bus operators send Vehicle/Crew (Driver)/Bus GPS Tracking information 15-30 minutes prior to Bus start time. Some bus operators may share only the boarding point contact number. You may use this boarding point contact number to coordinate with the bus crew to help you in boarding the bus. If you don't have this information and need help in bus boarding, please contact our customer care at support@abhibus.com. Our team will assist you in boarding the bus.

If you have an ongoing trip, please select the 'Ongoing Trip' section under main menu and select the booking to connect to an agent."}

{  "Category": "Booking Related",  "Sub-Category": "I booked duplicate ticket for the same journey",  "Question": "I've accidentally booked two tickets. What should I do now?",  "Answer": "In the Chatbot goto, the 'Cancellation' section under 'Booked Tickets' and select 'Duplicate Ticket Bookings' to view tickets that got booked recently. Identify the duplicate booking you want to cancel. Then select 'Yes' to go ahead with the cancellation. 

A super agent will be assigned to you after you select 'Yes' to help you in the cancellation of your duplicate ticket.

In case you cannot find the required booking in the 'Duplicate Ticket Bookings' section of the chatbot, then contact us immediately at support@abhibus.com with details of both the tickets. We will request the bus operator and try our best to issue a full refund for one of the bookings."}

